---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy — Thee Rainers"
  description="How Thee Rainers uses cookies. Short answer: we don't use tracking or advertising cookies."
>
  <section class="bg-[#F7F5F2] px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20 pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">

      <p class="text-[#D4A373] text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-black text-[#141414] text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight tracking-tight mb-3">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-[#141414]/40 text-sm mb-12">Last updated: 26 May 2026</p>

      <div class="prose-legal">

        <h2>The short version</h2>
        <p>
          We do not use advertising cookies, tracking cookies, or profiling cookies. There is no cookie consent banner on this site because no non-essential cookies are set by us.
        </p>

        <h2>What is a cookie?</h2>
        <p>
          A cookie is a small text file stored in your browser by a website you visit. Cookies serve different purposes: some are strictly necessary to make a website function, others collect analytics data, and others track your behaviour across sites for advertising.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies we set</h2>
        <p>We do not set any first-party cookies. The following strictly necessary cookie may be set by our infrastructure provider:</p>

        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Set by</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>__cf_bm</code></td>
              <td>Cloudflare</td>
              <td>Bot management and security. Identifies automated traffic to protect the site. Strictly necessary — cannot be disabled without breaking core security functions.</td>
              <td>30 minutes</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong>. This tool is privacy-first by design: it does not use cookies, does not store IP addresses, and does not track individual users across sessions or sites. It collects only aggregate, anonymous data (page views, referrer, country-level geographic data). No consent is required for cookieless analytics.
        </p>
        <p>We do not use Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, Facebook Pixel, TikTok Pixel, or any other cookie-based analytics or advertising tool.</p>

        <h2>Third-party cookies from embedded content</h2>
        <p>
          Some pages on this site embed third-party content that may set cookies in your browser:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>YouTube video embeds</strong> — The Library page (<a href="/library">/library</a>) embeds YouTube videos using the standard YouTube player. YouTube may set cookies when you interact with or view these videos. The token-gated Workshop Replay page uses <code>youtube-nocookie.com</code>, which YouTube states does not set cookies until you interact with the video.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not control cookies set by third-party platforms. For YouTube's cookie practices, refer to Google's privacy policy at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Payment processing</h2>
        <p>
          When you click a purchase button, you are redirected to Stripe's hosted checkout at <code>checkout.stripe.com</code>. Any cookies set during that process are set by Stripe on their own domain and are governed by <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe's Privacy Policy</a>. No Stripe tracking scripts are loaded on theerainers.com.
        </p>

        <h2>How to control cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You can manage and delete cookies through your browser settings. Instructions for common browsers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
          <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
          <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Blocking strictly necessary cookies (such as <code>__cf_bm</code>) may affect the security and functionality of the site.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:rainers@stepintoring.com">rainers@stepintoring.com</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal {
    color: #141414;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: #141414;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .prose-legal p, .prose-legal li {
    color: #141414;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }
  .prose-legal ul {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .prose-legal a {
    color: #c84d3a;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .prose-legal a:hover {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }
  .prose-legal strong {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #141414;
  }
  .prose-legal code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: rgba(20,20,20,0.06);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .prose-legal table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .prose-legal th {
    background: rgba(20,20,20,0.05);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(20,20,20,0.12);
    color: #141414;
  }
  .prose-legal td {
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(20,20,20,0.12);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .prose-legal tr:nth-child(even) td {
    background: rgba(20,20,20,0.025);
  }
</style>
